Trump. She tweeted it herself,

31:09.067 --> 31:11.870 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the H. was there.

31:11.870 --> 31:19.978 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that the backlash is
immediate and has come from all
ranges of candidates on

31:19.978 --> 31:24.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Republican side and on the
Democratic side. This is not one
of those things where

31:24.349 --> 31:28.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they're just sort of backing
away and saying Trump will be
Trump. Pretty much of all the

31:28.420 --> 31:34.126 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
